The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec. 30 (PTI): Delhi High Court has held that the income of an accident victims family members should not have any bearing on the compensation.           
	The court disagreed with the motor accident claim tribunal, which considered the earnings of the victims wife while fixing the compensation in a road accident.                   
	 Kottayam (PTI): An 18-month-old boy on Tuesday slipped out of his mothers arms from a speeding bus in Kottayam and fell on the road but escaped serious injuries. Ambily was standing near the front door of the crowded bus when it took a sharp turn, jolting the baby out of her grip. Tom was unconscious but was out of danger after first aid.                   
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): A woman was arrested on Monday for allegedly marrying over a dozen times and cheating elderly men. Seema alias Afsari, 31, was arrested after a person complained his wife had fled with jewellery worth lakhs and Rs 85,000 in cash. Afsaris real husband, Mohammed Shahid, 40, has also been arrested for alleged involvement in the racket.                  
	 Chennai (PTI): A 48-year-old Ugandan, who has allegedly been living in Chennai for the past 30 years without a passport, was arrested on Tuesday. Charles Arabakoko had been living in with a woman. His landlord had complained about him.                   
	 Kochi (PTI): A couple has exchanged wedding vows wearing ornaments crafted from coconut shells. Elizabeth Varghese also wore a wrist watch made of coconut shells. The ornaments, costing about Rs 40,000, were crafted by Anigar, a craftsman from Thrissur.                  
	 Bhavnagar (PTI): A 19-year-old girl has been arrested for allegedly burying her newborn baby alive in a village in Bhavnagar. The unwed mother buried the boy a few hours after the delivery. A man who saw the babys legs jutting out of the ground informed the police.                                                                                                                         
